# QEMU Functional Validation for libnn

Build and run libnn unit tests on QEMU to verify functional correctness after code changes.

## Quick Start (Recommended)

Use the scripts in `qemu-validate/`:

```bash
cd /home/nick/work/libnn/qemu-validate

# Step 1: Build the library
bash build_libnn.sh --verbose

# Step 2: Run a single function test on QEMU
bash run_qemu_test.sh conv_HWC_s8_s8_s8_asym_bias_any --strace
```

### build_libnn.sh

Builds `libnn.a` for a target CPU. Must run before QEMU or FPGA tests.

```bash
bash build_libnn.sh [--cpu NAME] [--vec-cfg CFG] [--verbose]
```

| Option | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `--cpu NAME` | ax45mpv | CPU build target |
| `--vec-cfg CFG` | zve64d | Vector config: zve32x, zve32f, zve64x, zve64f, zve64d |
| `--verbose` | off | Show full build output |

### run_qemu_test.sh

Compiles a single unit test against `libnn.a` and runs it on QEMU.

```bash
bash run_qemu_test.sh <test_name> [--vlen N] [--strace] [--perf] [--timeout N]
```

| Option | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `--vlen N` | 512 | Vector length: 128, 256, 512, 1024 |
| `--strace` | off | Capture output via strace (needed in sandboxed environments) |
| `--perf` | off | Performance mode: run only the large test case |
| `--timeout N` | 120 | QEMU timeout in seconds |

**Important**: Always use `--strace` when running from Claude Code, as QEMU's semihosting output goes to a non-stdout fd in sandboxed environments.

## Correctness Verification

Each unit test (`Examples/unit_func/t_*.c`) compares the function's output against pre-computed golden data stored in `Examples/unit_func/bin/*.bin`. The test prints:
- `accuracy checking pass` — output matches golden data within tolerance
- `accuracy checking fail` — mismatch detected

Most tests have 3 sub-tests (small/medium/large input sizes). All must pass.

## Running Full Test Suite

For full regression (294 unit tests):

```bash
cd /home/nick/work/libnn/project/ax45mpv
export QEMU_SYS_RV64=/local/nick/qemu_andes/build/qemu-system-riscv64
export PATH="/local/nick/SW_Release_cp/ast530/nds64le-elf-newlib-v5d/bin:/home/nick/work/libnn:$PATH"
bash ./run.sh
```

- `run.sh` uses `RUN_CONFIG=2` (QEMU mode) by default
- Default VLEN=512 (`riscv-qemu-wrapper-v512_d512_b512`)

